                  value: Decrease
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
                  value: Increase
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
                  value: Replace
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: CVMkWffJ7quAiCT1yuTA9Yfe2iFwZdCBMRUkJAvQowDL
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/math/QuantitySchedule
          description: |
            Specifies a quantity schedule to be associated to a financial product to represent a trade amount. This data type extends MeasureSchedule with several unit or multiplier attributes that are used to define financial quantities. This data type is generically based on a schedule and can also be used to represent a quantity as a single value.
          datedValue:
            description: |
              A schedule of step date and value pairs. On each step date the associated step value becomes effective. The step dates are used to order the steps by ascending order. This attribute is optional so the data type may be used to define a schedule with a single value.
            type:
              blueId: 6aehfNAxHLC1PHHoDr3tYtFH3RWNbiWdFancJ1bypXEY
            itemType:
              blueId: 4Goc1Ax7PdSp2KoLBDYnqrtvCeRBneZD8E97GQazSXQv
            schema:
              minItems:
                type:
                  blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
                value: 0
          frequency:
            description: |
              Defines the frequency to be used when defining a quantity. For example a quantity may be specified as a number of barrels of oil per day, which needs multiplying by the number of days in the relevant period to get the total quantity as a number of barrels.
            type:
              blueId: JCn7SJcxSE4UKZYvi2YchB4nwjTsdYKvhCc7RnYogigz
          multiplier:
            description: |
              Defines an optional number that the quantity should be multiplied by to derive a total quantity. This number is associated to a unit. For example in the case of the Coal (API2) CIF ARA (ARGUS-McCloskey) Futures Contract on the CME, where the unit would be contracts, the multiplier value would 1,000 and the mulitiplier unit would be 1,000 MT (Metric Tons).
            type:
              blueId: BCRUUCDz5YoH72WRdFUdE8hpNrxmqAyK6QzZdV91WaHp
          unit:
            description: |
              Qualifies the unit by which the amount is measured. Optional because a measure may be unit-less (e.g. when representing a ratio between amounts in the same unit).
            type:
              blueId: 7UDCVn3tDYHeQBU818n6bFdccjBeDPrc6GddKWkT4WDu
          val:
            description: |
              Specifies the value of the measure as a number. Optional because in a measure vector or schedule, this single value may be omitted.
            type:
              blueId: 7pwXmXYCJtWnd348c2JQGBkm9C4renmZRwxbfaypsx5y
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 6dk5GwNi2WVW1WtdQX75yiMvujuqv21d4kneiqK6QKzT
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/math/Rounding
          description: Defines rounding rules and precision to be used in the rounding of a number.
          precision:
            description: |
              Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places when the number is evaluated in decimal form (not percentage), e.g. 0.09876543 rounded to the nearest 5 decimal places is  0.0987654.
            type:
              blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
          roundingDirection:
            description: Specifies the rounding rounding rule as up, down, or nearest.
            type:
              blueId: GiWBNc37iwwMQdVLNNuNgT9Sz81v1zvwUB1G98aPvqa4
            schema:
              required:
                type:
                  blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
                value: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: ArfQ58kSzN4QkRNkhhMYbmgBrEGPrnnSSA4sgC1Stoho
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/math/RoundingDirectionEnum
          description: |
            The enumerated values to specify the rounding direction and precision to be used in the rounding of a number.  Used by function cdm.base.math.RoundToPrecision.
          type:
            blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
          schema:
            enum:
              items:
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
                  value: Down
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
                  value: Nearest
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
                  value: Up
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: GiWBNc37iwwMQdVLNNuNgT9Sz81v1zvwUB1G98aPvqa4
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/math/RoundingModeEnum
          description: |
            The enumerated values to specify the rounding direction when rounding of a number to nearest.  Used by function cdm.base.math.RoundToNearest.
          type:
            blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
          schema:
            enum:
              items:
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
                  value: Down
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
                  value: Up
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: J8qh3m8ZL5ifRQhM8Vjoki2nGhcdXhkzvzX7MkCeP5pj
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/math/Schedule
          description: |
            A class defining a schedule of rates or amounts in terms of an initial value and then a series of step date and value pairs. On each step date the rate or amount changes to the new step value. The series of step date and value pairs are optional. If not specified, this implies that the initial value remains unchanged over time.
          datedValue:
            description: |
              The schedule of step date and value pairs. On each step date the associated step value becomes effective. A list of steps may be ordered in the document by ascending step date. An FpML document containing an unordered list of steps is still regarded as a conformant document.
            type:
              blueId: 6aehfNAxHLC1PHHoDr3tYtFH3RWNbiWdFancJ1bypXEY
            itemType:
              blueId: 4Goc1Ax7PdSp2KoLBDYnqrtvCeRBneZD8E97GQazSXQv
            schema:
              minItems:
                type:
                  blueId: 5WNMiV9Knz63B4dVY5JtMyh3FB4FSGqv7ceScvuapdE1
                value: 0
          val:
            description: The initial rate or amount, as the case may be. An initial rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.
            type:
              blueId: 7pwXmXYCJtWnd348c2JQGBkm9C4renmZRwxbfaypsx5y
            schema:
              required:
                type:
                  blueId: 4EzhSubEimSQD3zrYHRtobfPPWntUuhEz8YcdxHsi12u
                value: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 73UaBEmPjNZQT7mUS7Rdnxb9fLcnfsn84MCkvVALW3vw
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/math/UnitType
          description: Defines the unit to be used for price, quantity, or other purposes
          capacityUnit:
            description: |
              Provides an enumerated value for a capacity unit, generally used in the context of defining quantities for commodities.
            type:
              blueId: ANaFxPMcbPKw8USLSD7mcUeT9DBz5q9BkYYt9GMjvDMz
          currency:
            description: Defines the currency to be used as a unit for a price, quantity, or other purpose.
            type:
              blueId: F5GfdsSNcjLAm9anbfMQqxdxAFonErhU5UXFbQzq1zXY
          financialUnit:
            description: |
              Provides an enumerated value for financial units, generally used in the context of defining quantities for securities.
            type:
              blueId: FWBc9MZLyNP1UHpkesLTwX4uMpnMK6Tjr5QZnhvs2WRB
          weatherUnit:
            description: |
              Provides an enumerated values for a weather unit, generally used in the context of defining quantities for commodities.
            type:
              blueId: aUWGFpq6gwDP6zaku6dz6bnhGWzX5a3YSgTLJzSqXiL
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 7UDCVn3tDYHeQBU818n6bFdccjBeDPrc6GddKWkT4WDu
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/math/WeatherUnitEnum
          description: |
            Provides enumerated values for weather units, generally used in the context of defining quantities for commodities.
          type:
            blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
          schema:
            enum:
              items:
                - type:
                    blueId: DLRQwz7MQeCrzjy9bohPNwtCxKEBbKaMK65KBrwjfG6K
